reviewText: 1.MONEY IN THE BANK LADDER MATCH JEFF HARDY VS. KING BOOKER VS. FINLAY VS. MR. KENNEDY VS. CM PUNK VS. RANDY ORTON VS. EDGE 8.5/10 I EXPECTED A LOT OUT OF THIS MATCH. MR. KENNEDY WINS. 2. THE GREAT KHALI VS. KANE 3/10 THIS MATCH SUCKED! KHALI WINS. 3. UNITED STATES CHAMPIONSHIP MATCH MVP VS. CHRIS BENOIT 7/10 THIS MATCH WAS ALRIGHT. BENOIT WINS AND RETAINS THE UNITED STATES CHAMPIONSHIP. 4.WORLD HEAVYWEIGHT CHAMPIONSHIP MATCH BATISTA VS. UNDERTAKER 8.5/10 THIS MATCH WAS THE MATCH OF THE NIGHT BUT I REALLY EXPECTED A WHOLE LOT MORE OUT OF THIS MATCH. UNDERTAKER WINS AND BECOMES THE NEW WORLD HEAVYWEIGHT CHAMPION AND 15-0 AT WRESTLEMANIA. THIS MATCH SHOULD HAVE BEEN THE LAST MATCH OF THE NIGHT. 5. ECW ORIGINALS VS. THE NEW BREED 5/10 THIS WAS A STUPID MATCH. ECW ORIGINALS WIN. 6. BATTLE OF THE MILLIONARES/HAIR VS. HAIR MATCH. ECW WORLD CHAMPION BOBBY LASHLEY W/ DONALD TRUMP VS. INTERCONTINENTAL CHAMPION UMAGA W/ MR.MCHMOHN 6/10 THIS WAS A DUMB MATCH BUT FUNNY. LASHLEY AND TRUMP WIN AND MR. MCHMOHN GETS HIS HEAD SHAVED BALD. 7. WOMENS CHAMPIONSHIP MATCH ASHLEY VS. MELINA 0/10 SKIP. MELINA RETAINS. 8. WWE CHAMPIONSHIP MATCH JOHN CENA VS. SHAWN MICHEALS. 8.5/10 THIS WAS A PRETTY GOOD MATCH IT WOLD HAVE BEEN BETTER IF CENA DIDNT RETAIN THE WWE CHAMPIONSHIP BUT HE DID. 1-2-3 CENA SUCKS! CENA SUCKS! CENA SUCKS!

reviewText: That's pretty much how I can describe it.  While watching it, it felt better than it actually was, but rethinking back, it was nowhere near the level of the previous two years' Wrestlemanias.Money in the BankEdge vs Matt Hardy vs King Booker vs Jeff Hardy vs Randy Orton vs Finlay vs CM Punk vs Kennedy KennedyIt came and went, and was above average, and it was short, and it was not as well-put together as the previous two years.  The most memorable high spot of course is the ladder spot with Jeff jumping onto Edge laid out on a ladder propped between the ring apron and the guard-rail, breaking the ladder in half.  It actually managed to look and sound better as a Youtube clip than on the event itself.  Crowd was almost completely dead for most of the beginning, and barely gave this ladder spot the pop it deserved.  (7/10)Kane vs The Great Khali(0/10)WWE United States ChampionshipMVP vs NO ONE WHO'S NAME DOES NOT RHYME WITH "BRIS END LAW"~!This one had a surprise twist in that MVP actually managed to out-wrestle the technical wrestler here, putting on some almost Angle/NO ONE chain wrestling as was seen in Wrestlemania X7.  The problem was that the crowd was completely dead for most of this (Just like Benoit a few months later, OH SNAPSZ~!  Terrible joke), and the match wasn't as long as it should likely have been.  (7/10)World Heavyweight ChampionshipBatista (C) w/o BASKETBALLS~! vs the Undertaker w/ Druids to waste five minutes with piped-in chantingSmackdown main event practically a curtain jerker as the third match on the card?  BAAAHAHAHAHAH!  This was one match that felt better when watching it than it actually was.  Further retrospective reflection shows that the Undertaker carried most of the match, as he did with Mark Henry in Wrestlemania 22, but this was no classic match.  (5/10)ECW Originals vs NEW BREEDTommy Dreamer, Sabu, Sandman, Rob Van Dam vs Marcus Cor Von, Elijah Burke, Matt Striker, Kevin ThornThe match almost made me cry as the audience was absolutely DEAD for the entire first half of the match.  No pops for anyone but Rob Van Dam.  This is just to show you just how much the WWE cares about pushing the ECW originals and getting the crowd behind them (hint, not at all).  The audiene finally started to make noise at some point in the middle.  Mildly entertaining match killed by total crowd apathy and piss-poor hype buildup.  (6/10)A note on the matches thus far and to come, considering how this crowd is supposedly recordbreaking 80,103 people, I expect a damn lot of noise from them, and thus far they're behaving like a half-empty 2,000 full arena; it didn't sound anywhere near as loud as 80,000 people at any moment in the event.BATTLE OF THE BILLIONAIRES~!Vince McMahon | Umaga vs Donald Trump | Bobby "Lindsay"How painfully stupidly awkward this publicity stunt was.  And it -was- a publicity stunt.  Not hard to believe how badly WWE was doing at this point in time ratings-wise that they needed to do this.  Seeing Donald Trump pretend to be interested in wrestling and the soap opera-ish kayfabe of it was embarassing.  Seeing Trump awkwardly clothesline Vince McMahon, and do a piss-poor job of selling Stone Cold's stunner was embarassing.  The match itself was straight out of Umaga's Royal Rumble match against John Cena --- Umaga utterly squashed Bobby Lashley, but since McMahon's an idiot who kept screwing with Stone Cold rather than let Umaga kill Bobby Lashley, Stone Cold flips and beats up Umaga so Lashley can steal a win.Seriously, the ending was never in doubt; you honestly think uptight Donald Trump is going to be shaved bald instead of Vince McMahon?  Say what you will about McMahon as a promoter or a booker, but he is an amazing boss in that he will go all-out and do anything to entertain people, even if he goes overboard by inserting his character into places it should not be (ie, the center of the Invasion angle, overshadowing the fatal four way at Wrestlemania 2000), he still puts his body on the line all the time.  He is as Alexander the Great was; right there in the front lines with his men.  He does everything he asks his wrestlers to do, from wrestling to high spots and bumps to humiliation.  I commend Vince McMahon for that, but I cannot commend stupid stunts like this match was.  (2/10)WWE Women's ChampionshipAshley vs Melina.  Who the hell cares who was champion to start?Reviewer "Cryza" says that the Women's championship should never be defended at Wrestlemania.  I would have argued against that if it weren't ASHLEY MASSARO wrestling in this garbage match.  But for the time being, as the WWE hires more models and less female wrestlers, it will be a fact that women's matches will almost always suck.  (0/10)WWE ChampionshipJohn Cena (C) vs Shawn MichaelsSince this was deep in the reign of Superman Cena as the undefeated "exalted one" who would never lose the championship to anyone short of God Himself, and even then he would need an immediate rematch the next day to win it back.  Many superstars have been booked in this sort of way but unlike them all, Cena did not have the wrestling skill or the charisma to back it up.At first I thought it was just an occasional occurrence, but this match is the third instance in which I saw John Cena's strength---getting beat up on.John Cena has this amazing ability to bring out the very best in his opponent; in making them beat on him so thoroughly and passionately that it feels like the bookers make you eat their underwear when Cena wins it after his opponent puts on a match of a lifetime performance.Wrestlemania 21: JBL puts on the absolute best match of his life, dominating Cena for a good 90% of the match, only to lose in an ass way after having been on the dominating end for the last few minutes.Royal Rumble 2007: Cena gets more offense in, but Umaga just sells MONSTER HEEL to new heights and levels in the absolute best match of his career, but SUPER CENA NEEDS TO RETAIN, DAMMIT!  Invisible white boy rapper with square jaw and monkey face = MONEY~!And so in this match, the very same Shawn Michaels who in the last year's Wrestlemania I called a great entertainer but a poor wrestler, puts on a spellbindingly entertaining wrestling match, with absolutely unbelievable psychology (Michaels wants to shake Cena's hand at the beginning, Cena refuses, Michaels absolutely brutalizes him and screams at him, slaps him around, mocks and taunts him, then refuses Cena's handshake at the end), and while Cena put in even more offense than at the Royal Rumble, he was still little more than a stumpy roid ranger who did little more than F-U's, clotheslines, punches, and generic hoss offense, while Shawn Michaels MADE this match.  (7/10)And just like the Smackdown main event at Wrestlemania 21, Cena gets his ass beat by an opponent who goes all out like an exterminator using a laser death ray on a cockroach or a soldier using an air strike to take out a single enemy soldier, and yet STILL Super Cena wins it, because he's John Cena and Vince McMahon cannot bear to have him be pinned by anyone.And the crowd mirrored this sentiment, as in the beginning HALF the people were for Shawn Michaels, and HALF were for John Cena, and by the middle of it, almost EVERYONE was for Shawn Michaels, and only the kids were still for John Cena.  You could clearly tell the tones of the crowd, as the cheers for Shawn Michaels were louder, lower, and throatier, while the cheers for John Cena had virtually no bass to them, and were too high to include women.On the whole, the matches were decent enough for a Wrestlemania, but the overall booking was subpar, the crowd was pathetically out of it for almost everything but the main event, and there was way too much in the way of filler and time-wasting like repeating overly-dramatic hype videos and the 10 minute entrances before the BATTLE OF THE BILLIONAIRES~! match.

reviewText: Money in the Bank-Ladder Match (Jeff Hardy vs Matt Hardy vs CM Punk vs Edge vs Mr.Kennedy vs King Booker vs Finlay vs Randy Orton) - Nice match, and a great way to kick off wrestlemania. Better than the first, but worse than last year's. Jeff and Edge are involved in an insane spot. Nice usage of weapons and ladders, and in the end Mr.Kennedy takes the briefcase, and loses it to Edge later the same year. 4/5Kane vs The Great Khali - The Great Khali is a terrible wrestler. Even worse than this match, is that they made him win the heavyweight title later this year. Worst match this year easily. Khali wins after a chokeslam 1.5/5Chris Benoit vs MVP (US Title Match) - These two were/are good wrestlers both. MVP should've won the title here, rather than at Judgement Day, because this was easily the better match. Awesome technical wrestling. Benoit uses the Diving Headbutt to end this one. 4.5/5Batista vs Undertaker (World Heavyweight Championship match) - Batista is usually a kind of boring wrestler, and Undertaker is too. But this match was great. Batista's Powerslam through the table was great. I don't really care for either wrestler, but they really showed their best here. UT wins with a Tombstone. 5/5ECW Originals vs The New Breed - A quite short match. It would've been a pretty stupid match if the New Breed had won. That's why it was quite predictable, the ECW Originals were great here, The New Breed... not so much. Ends like it should, 5-Star Frog Splash. 2.5/5Bobby Lashley vs Umaga (Battle of the Billionaires, Special Referee Steve Austin) - This was basically Donald Trump vs Vince McMahon, who picked wrestlers for themselves. Lashley defeates Umaga after a Stunner and a Spear, after which Vince gets shaved bald. 3/5Ashley Massaro vs Melina (Women's Championship) - Melina can't wrestle, Massaro isn't great either, but she should've won. I'm not big on the whole WWE Diva scene right now, cause only few can wrestle. For them being eye candy is an other thing. Anyway, Melina won, retaining the title. 2/5John Cena vs Shawn Michaels (WWE Championship) - This was a nice match. Bad ending though. The Spike Piledriver to the steel steps was the high point in this one. Cena, gaining almost no offensive in this match however, locks Michaels in the STF-U and wins. God I hate Cena. But it doesn't takeaway from a great match. 4/5Overall it was a good, but not great WM. Wrestlemania XX is still the best.
summary: Worse than last year's, but better than 21

reviewText: April 1st, 2007 was the date in which Wrestlemania 23 eminated from Ford Field in Detroit, Michigan. With an "estimated" (meaning slightly inflated, but not by Wrestlemania III standards) 80,000 fans on tap, they saw an ezciting show that provided entertainment at almost all turns. I'm not going review every thing, but just some highlights.3 Best Matches:- Money in the Bank III: When I first saw this was going to be an 8-man match (as opposed to the 6 from the prior two Wrestlemanias), I thought this was going to be a cluster-(fill in swear suffix here). 8 men, a few ladders, this had to be diastorous. But what a fun disaster it was as all eight men worked their tails off to make this match a great 20 minute opener for 'Mania. My two personal favorite moments both included Booker: When he finds the step-ladder (that was cute), and then when he had to decide between Sharmell and the briefcase, and JBL exclaimed, "Common Booker! I've left plenty of women during my lifetime!". Anyways, Kennedy's fireman's carry on Hornswoggle and that splash Jeff Hardy did onto Edge must be seen to be believed.- MVP vs. Chris Benoit (RIP, even if you killed your family): I always knew MVP had potential, and under Benoit's wing, he only improved. This may not have been their best match (Backlash was a tad better), but it definitely had its moments, with Benoit winning by headbutt for the first time in forever.- Batista vs. Undertaker: Came out forth due to Batista's questionable style, and when you first see this match, both men look incredibly pissed, and its easy to see why. However, they tore down the house, and Batista's best match since he came back 8 months prior. Undertaker's win streak survives, to everyone's liking, but a torn bicep would cut that reign short.Honorable Mention: John Cena vs. HBK: A long match (in the beginning), and the wrong man won (imagine Hell in a Cell with HBK and Taker again?!?!). HBK did carry Cena to a more-than-acceptable match (piledriver on the steps!), and though he lost in blood, HBK had nothing to be ashamed by.Other things:-Special Features: Not much, just some extra promos and matches. That tag team lumberjack match was short and featured frustrating burials of Ric Flair and Carlito from the main card (even if they did win this match). You see the No Way Out rematch from a week before 'Mania, and you see the "All Grown Up" promos.- Hall of Fame: Buy the DVD even only for this disc. With excellent speeches by most everyone (I know that Shatner was probably the worst, and Todd Grisham did not do too badly with his hosting skills), it was great to hear the stories of yesteryear. Seriously, this disc was, as Triple H would say, "That Damn Good!"Overall, this DVD will only go up in value as years go buy, and its tin is great covering. Buy it, even if it is only for the HOF.
summary: One of the best WWE DVD releases of the year!

reviewText: So this is a very good dvd. Having the hall of fame included is awesome. But...why in the heck does Wrestlemania 23 on this dvd begin with the intro from wrestlemania 3? It starts with a wide shot of the Pontiac Silverdome, with the caption "March 29, 1987" on the bottom. Then the camera changes to the center of the ring where a very young Vince McMahon stands and announces "Welcome to Wrestlemania 3!" Then Wrestlemania 23 actually begins. Could someone explain this major discontinuity problem? Oh well, if it were not for this I would have given the dvd 5 stars.

reviewText: Jeff Hardy Vs. Matt Hardy Vs. King Booker Vs. Finlay Vs. C.M. Punk Vs. Mr. Kennedy Vs. Randy Orton Vs. Edge (Money In The Bank Ladder Match) - This was the opener for WM and it was pretty good. Last year's MITB was better but it did have one high spot with Jeff Hardy putting Edge through a ladder! It ends when Mr. Kennedy prevents C.M. Punk from reaching the briefcase and claims it himself. A good way to start off WM.Kane Vs. The Great Khali - Got to give Kane credit, he tried to make Khali look awesome but just couldn't. Sad because Khali DOES have a good look but just no skill. He can't even make his basic moves look that painful. It did have a "nod" moment to WrestleMania III when Kane slammed Khali but that was it. Khali wins with his weak-a** version of the chokeslam.Chris Benoit Vs. MVP (WWE U.S. Title Match) - This match proves that Benoit should be in the Hall Of Fame one day because he made MVP look very good. The best that I've seen him and helped him start the roll that he is on now. Ends when Benoit (after failing in several submission attempts at both the crossface and the sharpshooter) uses his flying headbutt to finish off MVP and retain the title.NOTE: I wrote this review before the tragic events that took place between June 23-25 involving Chris Benoit. This match now makes me sad that such a talented individual will forever be known as a man that murdered his family. Despite the fact that doctors have now discovered that Chris Benoit had brain damage and that he may have had dementia which can lead to irrational actions (I know because a family member once tried to kill me as a child and he had similiar brain damage), his career will be overshadowed by this horrible tragedy.The Undertaker Vs. Batista (World Heavyweight Championship) - Before I begin, let me say that I agree with most fans in that this match should've been last! All due respect to the fabulous WWE title match, this one deserved to go last.Now, as for this match, this one was a sprint but a very good sprint! This has to be Batista's best match since his Hell In The Cell match with Triple H in 2005. These two hit power move after power move and kept coming back for more. I especially loved when "The Animal" powerslammed "The Dead Man" through the ECW commentator's table! Ends when UT gets his Tombstone piledriver. Great bout!ECW Originals Vs. The New Breed - This one was okay but the re-match two nights later on ECW On SciFi was much better as it was under hardcore rules! Overall, not bad but being that this was WrestleMania, this one is the one that SHOULD'VE been under Hardcore rules.Bobby Lashley Vs. Umaga - This was the "Battle Of The Billionares" match with "Stone Cold" Steve Austin as the referee. The match was average but the storyline is what made it entertaining. Ends when Lashley spears Umaga after receiving a "Stunner" from Austin! From there, per pre-match stipulation, Vince McMahon gets shaved bald! Donald Trump also gets stunned by Austin after the shaving.Ashley Vs. Melina (WWE Women's Title Match) - Weakest match on the card without a doubt and I am not saying this because its the women because there has been some great women's title matches at PPV's. This wasn't one of them! About the only thing good about this match is that Melina retained the belt and seeing all those beautiful women get inside the ring and rumble!Shawn Michaels Vs. John Cena (WWE Title Match) - This match I have to say was, for the most part, dominated by Shawn. Cena is, at best, a compentent grappler with plenty of charisma. Shawn has as much charisma plus more talent! I didn't expect much from this bout BUT this one I really enjoyed though I still feel UT/Batista should've been last!As for this match, it was a good way to end the card. I personally think Shawn should've won this one BUT business is business.This set also comes with plenty of extras including the Hall Of Fame show on Disc 3! Worth a buy!
summary: Not The Best WrestleMania But Its Still Good

reviewText: I think it is nonsense that you have to shed out a few more bucks to get the Hall of Fame Ceremony which in years past was part of the WM DVD. Furthemore the Hall of Fame DVD included here was disappointing. While I grew up with all these wrestlers and I am a big old school fan, its good to see them but its disrecpectful to them and the fans to not include a few matches from their respective careers.  Obviously I don't mean Dusty Rhodes or Jerry Lawler who already have their own DVD compilations.  While NIck Bockwinkel, Mr, Fuji, The Sheik, or The Wild Samoans wont sell huge DVD complimations there were no matches for any of them considering the contributions and entertainment they made to WWE and us fans.  Instead boring vingettes of current WWE stars "All Grown Up".  Who cares plus most of them are contained on the WM card in between matches.As for the WM 23 Wrestling is some of the best in years.  While WM 23 wont go down as one of the best of all time, the wrestling is damn good from top to bottom.  If you must skip the ultimate edition comp and just get the WM 23 DVD.  Or go to Best Buy where they pretty much priced them the same.
summary: Good Wrestling But WWE MIssed the Mark on this DVD

reviewText: The following below are the offical match results as seen from WrestleMania 23 on April 1st, 2007.Ok, first of all I was a bit disappointed with some things before WrestleMania even took place on Sunday April 1st. The fact that Hulk Hogan should have been in that match with Great Khali(to duplicate the WrestleMania III moment), The ECW world title should have been defended. The contestants in the Money in the Bank should have been more carefully picked. And the Cruiserweight title which was held by Gregory Helms for over a year at the time was suddenly stripped of his waist 1 month before Wrestlemania, and no tag team gold was included on the card either.The 3rd Annual Money in the Bank Ladder MatchWinner: Mr. KennedyRaiting: 7.5/10I was upset to see Kennedy win, but it could be worse. I think that Randy Orton should have won because he really needs a decent push to work with, considering he won the title 3 years ago and he cannot even compete in a WWE Championship match anymore. Finlay was a mistake to put in this match so was Booker T., both of them should have been in a 3 way match with Chris Benoit competing for the U.S. Championship in what would be the best  United States title match ever. I think that Hardocre Holly, and MVP should have taken their places. The match was overall good, im not sure if it surpassed last years MITBM but it could have been better this year, considering talent like Edge and Jeff Hardy were out the first 5 minutes going in the match.The Great Khali Vs. KaneWinner: Great KhaliRaiting: 3.5/10Somebody please explain to me why this match even took place. There was not even a stipulation like a body slam match or a last man standing match...Just a ridiculous singles match and a waste of talent. Probably better than last years Booker and Boogeyman match I would say.The United States ChampionshipChris Benoit Vs. MVPWinner: Chris BenoitRaiting: 5.5/10This match should have never taken place either. Chris Benoit should have wrestled in a triple threat against Finlay and Booker T,and I guarentee you that it would have been an amazing match, Benoit competed with these men in some of the best matches ever seen back in WCW. Instead they put MVP who I think should have been in the Money in the Bank ladder match instead. The match started off pretty good, but it became an uninteresting match, some great counters though.The World Heavyweight TitleBatista Vs. The UndertakerWinner: The UndertakerRaiting: 8.5/10This was a great match, Batista looked more aggressive than usual, kind of rekindled the spirit of the heel Batista we used to watch back when he was in Evolution in 2004. Undertaker showed great athlethism in the match. Both men kicking out of each other's finishing moves. Undertaker still rules the WrestleMania ring after being undefeated 15-0, finally the dead man rises once again!!ECW Originals Vs. The New BreedWinners: The ECW OriginalsRaiting: 6/10Is it just me or were the fans screwed when they watched this match. Lets see WWE resurrected the ECW name just to have a 8-man tag match at the grandest stage of all!? there was a big amount of disappointment in this match, there was no stipulation, no hardcore rules? no eliminations? What happened!?! Decent to watch but its to upsetting to watch great talent go to waste. Paul Heyman had to be happy after watching his pride possesion turn into a teletubby warfare.The Battle of the BillionairesUmaga w/ Mr. McMahon Vs. Bobby Lashley w/ Donald TrumpHair Vs. Hair Match with special referee Stone Cold Steve AustinWinner(s): Bobby Lashley with Donald TrumpRaiting: 8/10This match I have to say was very entertaining. It was cool to see Stone Cold return to WrestleMania. And Umaga and Lashley put on a great match. There were certain parts of the match that I like such as Stone Cold stunning Umaga and Lashley spearing him. I also like the part when Shane came in and did his "coast to coast" move on the top rope. In the end McMahon had his head shaved but it was a bit too dramatic if you ask me. Mr.McMahon should go see TMNT because he's got a big role in it as Splinter. Stone Cold stunned Trump which was also cool. In the end it was a fun match to watch.Womens Championship Lumberjill MatchWinner: MelinaRaiting: 4.5/10Another disappointing match, I actually thought this would be a good match but it was 2 minutes of un-entertaining wrestling. Melina can actually wrestle a little. Its Ashley who is un-trained and all she did was mostly kicks and punches. I did believe that Mickie James and Victoria would go against Melina in a triple Threat for the title but i was wrong again. To be honest it was more fun watching the divas than the actual match.WWE Championship MatchJohn Cena Vs. Shawn MichaelsWinner: John CenaRaiting: 10/10Alot of people don't realize some of the best matches in the history of professional wrestling. If you look back at WrestleManias in the past there are some matches that are just amazing to watch and get you caught up in the passion of the sport, the athlethism, and charisma. This was one of them.From start to finish this match was a knockout! even more entertaining than last year's WWE championship match. Watching this match gave me goosebumps because it had some nostalgic feeling that I cannot even explain. There was plenty of reversals, plenty of suspensful moments in the match where people were literally on their feet watching at home. HBK put up a valiant effort during the match but tapped out just as his friend Triple H did at last year's WrestleMania 22. Shawn Michaels actually gave a performance we have longed to see since WrestleMania 12. The best match of 2007 thus far.Thank you for checking out my review for WrestleMania 23!

reviewText: The results of this year's wrestlemania won't sit well with all those cena haters who made their way over to detroit from last year's mania. However, the fans at ford field and around the world witnessed the phenom, the undertaker pin batista following a tombstone piledriver and extend his mania win streak to 15 , but more importantly, become the new world heavyweight champion! This match featured multiple near falls: Batista kicking out of the last ride, taker kicking out of the batista bomb, and batista kicking out of the chokeslam. Great effort displayed by both wrestlers. But i was particularly pleased that undertaker emerged the winner. Another exciting match was the battle of the billionaires. In addition to lashley pinning umaga and vince's head being shaved bald, i especially enjoyed seeing austin stun donald trump after the match. This match kept me intrigued from start to finish and of course the austin beer drinking aftermath. The money in the bank briefcase was obtained by Mr. Kennedy. This disappointed me because randy orton or cm punk deserved to get a push. This was another intriguing match which featured orton giving the rko to cm punk from the top of the ladder. Great match.The fourth good match at this event was cena vs. hbk. We all knew that hbk wasn't going to win because he is heading into knee surgery. However, i cannot for the life of me root for someone like cena. Call old fashioned but i feel he lacks real wrestling abitlity in terms of innovation and variety( he uses similiar moves in all his matches). The match however featured good drama and intensity. The end of the bout came when cena reapplied the stfu in the middle of ring and hbk tapped out. Even though the outcome of this match does not sit well with alot of fans, it was a good physical match. I was disappointed that wwe decided to put the batista/taker match early in the event. Taker won the royal rumble which earns him the right to be in the main event, the last match of the ppv. I really didn't get that.  I was also disappointed with the women's title match. The new breed/originals match was pretty good and it was nice to see benoit retain his title against mvp. Kane vs. The not so great khali was forgettable.So, all in all, Mania 23 was a 4 out of 5 for me. 4 good matches means i will definitely purchase the three disc set when it comes out. I would recommend that you do the same. Thanks for reading. I'm out.
summary: Wrestlemania 23: Showcase of the Immortal ( Undertaker)

Kane- Not much you can say about this match, only thing that came out of it was Kane slamming Khali. Khali gets the win here. 2.3/5.Match#3  United States Championship: Chris Benoit(c) v. MVP- This was good match, I rememeber it being a technical one. MVP stepped that night and every time he was in the ring with Benoit. Benoit gets the win after a headbutt from the tope rope. 3.3/5.Match#4  World Heavyweight Championship: Batista(c) v. The Undertaker. "The Title vs. The Streak".This match was away better then I thought it would be. Damn near stole the show. Finishers. Tables. Hell of a Title match. But, The Undertaker gets the win and wins the World Title. Keepng the streak alive. 4/5.Match#5  The ECW Originals v. The New BreedThe match wasn't that long, but it was entertaining. Once it all broke down, RVD got the win with a Five Star Frog Splash. 2.7/5.Match#6  Hair v. Hair Match with Stone Cold as the Guest Referee. Lashley (w/ Trump) vs. Umaga (w/ Vince)This match was pretty good, epecially with all the build and energy behind. It was fun. Stone Cold wouldn't let any man push him around, classic Stone Cold. Some shenanigans from the McMahons. But it wouldn't help, Cause a stunner and spear sealed his fate. He was shaved bald. 3.5/5.Match#7  Lumberjill Match for the Women's Championship: Melina(c) v. AshleyThis match.. Lol. Bathroom break, for sure. 1.3/5.(Main Event) Match#8  WWE Championship: John Cena(c) v. Shawn MichaelsWow. I absolutley loved this match. A great main event! HBK is fantastic and Cena doesn't get enough credit, takes two to make a match. And having one of them being HBK does help out a lot. If you haven't this match, check it out. Crowd was awesome as well. Cena got the win after making HBK tapout to the STFU. Great WWE Title main event. Check this out. Very underated. 4.5/5.WMania23 was a really good show! Check it out, if you haven't. 7/10 stars.Extras.Lost of RAW and SD! segments.Exclusive interviews , countdowns, and vignettes.

reviewText: I was at this Wrestlemania in person.  I have been to seven Wrestlemanias.  This WM was average at best.  The two best matches were MVP/Benoit and Taker/Batista.  Batista is a horrible, no, HORRIBLE wrestler with a boring personality but Taker carried him through this match.  The ladder match was OK, but not as good as the last two Money in the Banks.  The one in LA was the best, and the one in Chicago was very good.  Definitely no classic matches or moments at this WM.  Nothing that will stick in people's minds like Steamboat/Savage, Hogan/Warrior, Rock/Austin, Angle/Michaels, Lesnar/Angle, or Foley/Edge at previous WM's.  This Wrestlemania isn't among the worst (WM20 is the worst, and WM13-16 are 4 bad ones) or the best.  I'd say just rent this one. If you want to add the best WM's to your collection, here are the ones to get:  WM3, WM6, WM8, WM17, and WM19.  Those are the 5 best.  Plus I'd buy WM18, which is worth the price just for the Rock/Hogan match.  Hope this helps.

reviewText: There's not a whole heck of a lot I can add to this one.  I'm sure most WWE fans have seen it, and I'm sure most fans agree on what's good and bad about "WrestleMania 23".  So, I'm gonna try a simple Pros & Cons List.*****PROS*****1) Most Of The Matches Are Worth A Watch---"WrestleMania 23" has 8 matches on the card, most of them enjoyable.  The RAW & SmackDown main events are very good title matches.  The Money-In-The-Bank Ladder Match --- while my least favorite to date --- is the kind of crazy action spotfest we like to see.  The Battle of the Billionaires is also a nice diversion; it's more about entertainment than wrestling, but it's a solid payoff.2) Detroit Crowd Was Hot From Most Of The Event---From the insane MITB Ladder Match opener to the patiently-paced main event between John Cena & Shawn Michaels.  The Battle of the Billionaires got a huge number of cheers & laughs for the most part.  The poor match between Great Khali & Kane even got some noise.  The Women's Title Match...well, that was doomed from the getgo.  Like it or not, a live audience can help or hurt some events.  "WrestleMania 23" is definitely better because of the Ford Field fans.3) Hall Of Fame Is Included On DVD---Although it pales in comparison to some of the recent ceremonies, this is still a pleasant viewing.  It's also the entire program, with no time limits placed on any of the speakers (as far as I know).4) Bonus Tag Team Contest---Carlito & Ric Flair (RAW) take on Chavo Guerrero & Gregory Helms (SmackDown) in the pre-show match.  "WrestleMania" always finds some way to bring out everyone who didn't get a match, making this one a Lumberjack Match.  Only problem...they put Ric Flair in the pre-show?!  Well, this was actually a punishment on Flair, but whatever.______________________________________________*****CONS*****1) Batista & Undertaker Should've Gone Last---I agree with just about everybody on this: Although John Cena & Shawn Michaels had the best match on the card in the main event spot, more fans were interested in seeing Batista/Undertaker showdown.  It had better buildup, and was a longer-running storyline.  Big props to HBK & Cena for their excellent contest, but Taker & Batista got a little shafted.2) The 4-Hour Length Is Wasted This Time---The big problem I have with "WrestleMania 23" being that long is because the matches aren't what make it that long.  Instead, there are a couple backstage segments that take up time, and they all are unfunny wastes of time.  In addition, the PPV keeps showing the All-Grown-Up commericals that hyped the event throughout the evening, and I frankly don't care about any of them.  In short, "WrestleMania 23" could've easily been a 3-hour event with some trimming, and it might've actually been more enjoyable way.3) Every Match On This PPV Has Been Outdone---Aside from the HBK/Cena main event, I don't believe anything on this PPV is "classic".  The Money-In-The-Bank Ladder Match is the worst of the 5 that this PPV series has presented.  Undertaker & Batista was a most pleasant surprise for many of us, but they outdid themselves as 2007 went on.  Chris Benoit & MVP also surprised many with their solid U.S. Title Match, but they also had much better matches in the weeks to come after this.  ECW's 8-Man Tag Team Match is a fun diversion, but nothing special in the grand scheme of things.  The Women's Title Match is a godawful mess; Khali/Kane ain't much better.  And many believe that HBK & Cena's hour-long encounter in England was a much better match than this one too.  So while "WM 23" has a decent lineup of matches, they all pale in comparison to other related matches.4) Lack Of Title Matches---There are four championship matches: 3 are quite good, and one is a boring mess.  But neither of the Tag Team Titles are present tonight, and the ECW & Intercontinental champs participated in the Battle of the Billionaires event.  I don't need every match to be for the gold, but if "WrestleMania" is the company's biggest event, I'd like to see more championship competition.  And it's not just "WM 23" that's been guilty of this in recent years.______________________________________________*****MY QUICK MATCH SCORES*****1) MONEY-IN-THE-BANK LADDER MATCH"7.0 / 10" (Even though some spots are bland or overused, the grueling effort these 8 guys put in can't be ignored.  This is a good match, but one of my least favorite matches in WWE history)2) THE GREAT KHALI V. KANE"4.0 / 10" (If there were more matches on the card, I wouldn't have been too upset that this giant-vs-giant affair was on the card.  But because of the shorter number of matches, this had more to deliver, and it failed.  Kane worked his tail off to make this work, but aside from the bodyslam to pay homage to Andre/Hogan from 20 years before in Detroit, this one is forgettable at best)3) MVP V. CHRIS BENOIT (champion) - UNITED STATES CHAMPIONSHIP"7.0 / 10" (Those of us who believed MVP would finally break through were right.  This techincal-style contest is a fine addition to the card.  I think most of their rematches are much better, but as a 1st time out, it's good enough.)4) BATISTA (champion) V. THE UNDERTAKER - WORLD HEAVYWEIGHT CHAMPIONSHIP"7.0 / 10" (These two worked their tails off to steal the show, and for many, they did.  I personally prefer some of their other matches together, but this a "WrestleMania"-caliber showdown that's worthy of Undertaker's annual prescence.  Batista also became much more entertaining after working with Taker.)5) ECW ORIGINALS V. THE NEW BREED"6.0 / 10" (While not a bad match, this brand deserved better since their ECW champion was stuck in a specialty showcase.  It's too bad their Extreme Rules rematch two nights later basically wiped the floor with this one.  But while it lasts, this is a fast-paced diversion that's fun to watch.)6) BATTLE OF THE BILLIONAIRES - HAIR VS. HAIR MATCHGUEST REFEREE - 'STONE COLD' STEVE AUSTINUMAGA (Intercontinental champion - w/ Vince McMahon) V.BOBBY LASHLEY (ECW World champion - w/ Donald Trump)"6.5 / 10" (You won't find many matches with as much star power or hype thrown into it.  Although Umaga & Lashley put on a solid physical contest, the ringside shenanigans with Trump, the McMahons, & Austin steal the show.  My biggest complaint is that this scenario all took more time than it needed, which would've allowed more time for a few other matches.  But as a unique marquee event, it's a good time.)7) WOMEN'S CHAMPIONSHIP - LUMBERJILL MATCHMELINA (champion) V. ASHLEY MASARRO"1.5 / 10" (A boring, botch-filled mess.  Melina was already capable of decent matches, but Ashley never became much to watch in the ring.  It's alright for WWE to find an excuse for their Divas to participate, but this match was so dreadful that the lively Detroit crowd finally stayed quiet.  And the massive catfight with all the Divas at the end makes no sense at all.  Skip It!)8) SHAWN MICHAELS V. JOHN CENA (champion) - WWE CHAMPIONSHIP"8.0 / 10" (Easily my favorite match on the card, with HBK & Cena developing a patiently-paced battle.  These two complement each other very well, most evident in a series of exciting counters towards the end of the match.  It's neat to see HBK be the dirtier opponent in the match, but with Cena still getting the most negative reaction.  This main event proves that HBK is among the greatest performers in pro wrestling history.  It also proves that no matter what, John Cena will continue to work his butt off to make a match work, even if it's a style that some hardcore enthusiasts won't embrace.  He's doing it for you, whether you want him to or not.)______________________________________________"WrestleMania 23" is worth adding to your collection, even though it's not a great package.  It's the rare event that you should own because it's a piece of history, regardless of quality.  Even though this PPV is ultimately a disappointment, sometimes we have to be grateful enough for the positives so that we forgive the negatives."WrestleMania 23" has earned my most half-hearted endorsement.
summary: Just Another Opinion From Another Fan

reviewText: I'll always have a soft spot for this WM, purely because it was the first WWE PPV I ever saw. I got into the WWE fairly recently, around January 2007 when we finally got Sky, the TV provider who shows WWE programming. I had to wait until my mother wanted to order a PPV (she watches too), and WM happened to be the first one.And I genuinelly thought this was a great show, it was better then WM22 and better then this year's WM24, in my opinion.This collector's edition tin case version is the one I own, it was the same price as the DVD on it's own so I thought I might as well as get it. I like the snazzy case, it looks really cool. The 3 DVDs are also cool.How about a run down of the matches, then?Money In The Bank match (Jeff Hardy vs King Booker vs Finlay vs CM Punk vs Mr Kennedy vs Matt Hardy vs Randy Orton vs Edge)A great way to begin the show, with this fast paced high flying match. It was a pretty good match - but out of 4 MITB matches to date, I think it's 3rd best (WM21 was the best, followed by WM24). The moment where Jeff leaps off the ladder onto Edge is amazing though. I didn't like Kennedy at the time, so I was unhappy he won. But overall, a solid match. (3.5/5)Interpromotional match (Kane vs The Great Khali)This match was boring. Kane did the best he could with a bad opponent, including an amazing moment where he bodyslammed Khali, but overall this match was disappointing as it's hard to find somebody who can make Khali good. (2/5)United States Championship (Chris Benoit vs MVP)I am not even going to mention the obvious and just concentrate on the match. This was a rather good match, and proved MVP can wrestle and can last the distance. Chris showed why he was a great in ring competitor. Another solid match. (3.5/5)World Heavyweight Championship (The Undertaker vs Batista)In my personal opinion, this match is vastly overrated. It was voted 2007's best match, but I disagree. Yes, it was a very good match but it wasn't the best of last year. There were some amazing moments and of course Undertaker winning was a highlight, but it was overhyped. Still I liked having Taker as champion, so it gets a high rating. (4/5)ECW Originals vs New BreedThis was the only ECW related match on the card and it didn't really live up to the hype. I'm glad the Originals won though, but I was hoping for more hardcore moments. Just average. (3/5)Battle Of The Billionaires Hair vs Hair Match (Bobby Lashley w/ Donald Trump vs Umaga w/ Vince McMahon with Stone Cold as Special Guest Referee)This match was a lot of fun, you can't deny that. It was great for a laugh and had loads of comedic moments. It was classic having Stone Cold as the referee as he wasn't afraid to get involved in the match. Everybody knew Vince would lose, but it was still hilarious to see him get his head shaved. A funny gimmicky match that provided some comic relief. (4.5/5)Women's Championship Lumberjill Match (Melina vs Ashley)I love the women's division, but this match wasn't WM standard. It was nothing compared to Mickie vs Trish from WM22. I dislike Melina and Ashley needs to go and learn how to wrestle better. The best bit was at the end where all the divas began brawling. This was just a match to calm everybody down before the main event. (2/5)WWE Championship (John Cena vs Shawn Michaels)Definitely without a doubt, the match of the night for me. But I may be biased as John & Shawn are my two favourite wrestlers. But this match was  legendary, only matched in brilliance by their hour long match in London a couple of weeks later. Shawn dominated most of the match, working on John's leg for most of it. After the referee got knocked out, chaos ensued. John got the win with the STFU. An absolutely EPIC match and a well deserved main event. (5+/5)This set also has the whole Hall Of Fame ceremony on disc 3 which I like to watch to see the superstars in the audience xDDisc 2 has extras - the best being the pre WM match, a tag team lumberjack match - Ric Flair & Carlito vs Gregory Helms & Chavo Guerrero, a rematch from No Way Out with Undertaker & Batista vs John Cena & Shawn Michaels and the segment where Bobby Lashley shows off Vince's bald head to the crowd on Raw (lol the bit where Vince tries to hide under Lillian's dress and Bobby rips it off is hilarious xD).Overall, a strong Wrestlemania with a great main event and a funny gimmicky match that holds it at 5 stars. Also the DVD is superbly made and I love the tin case. 5 starsd
